      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "THE RIGHT WAY (1) didn't measure up in the G2 Brisbane Cup last time out but will find this task much more to his liking. Has placed three from five over this distance range and gets a bunch of weight relief with the 3kg claim. Watch for a sharp spike in form. Former Victorian LEG DRIVE (4) hails from a handy family (half to G3 winner Violate) and looked good saluting at Toowoomba when having the first run for the new stable. Will have come on with that win now under the belt and can make his presence felt again. CONNECTICUT (6) is a two-time winner over this trip and will be ready to peak now fourth run back from a spell. Top-three contender on best figures. GALANO (2) is one from one around this circuit and is another to get some weight off. In the mix. FORTY TIMES (7) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.",
